schema.name: Q1
schema.sql: SELECT DayOfWeek, count(*) AS c FROM ontime WHERE Year >= 2000 AND Year <= 2008 GROUP BY DayOfWeek ORDER BY c DESC;

schema.name: Q2
schema.sql: SELECT DayOfWeek, count(*) AS c FROM ontime WHERE DepDelay>10 AND Year >= 2000 AND Year <= 2008 GROUP BY DayOfWeek ORDER BY c DESC;

schema.name: Q3
schema.sql: SELECT Origin, count(*) AS c FROM ontime WHERE DepDelay>10 AND Year >= 2000 AND Year <= 2008 GROUP BY Origin ORDER BY c DESC LIMIT 10;

schema.name: Q4
schema.sql: SELECT IATA_CODE_Reporting_Airline AS Carrier, count() FROM ontime WHERE DepDelay>10 AND Year = 2007 GROUP BY Carrier ORDER BY count() DESC;

schema.name: Q5
schema.sql: SELECT IATA_CODE_Reporting_Airline AS Carrier, avg(cast(DepDelay>10 as Int8))*1000 AS c3 FROM ontime WHERE Year=2007 GROUP BY Carrier ORDER BY c3 DESC;

schema.name: Q6
schema.sql: SELECT IATA_CODE_Reporting_Airline AS Carrier, avg(cast(DepDelay>10 as Int8))*1000 AS c3 FROM ontime WHERE Year>=2000 AND Year <=2008 GROUP BY Carrier ORDER BY c3 DESC;

schema.name: Q7
schema.sql: SELECT IATA_CODE_Reporting_Airline AS Carrier, avg(DepDelay) * 1000 AS c3 FROM ontime WHERE Year >= 2000 AND Year <= 2008 GROUP BY Carrier;

schema.name: Q8
schema.sql: SELECT Year, avg(DepDelay) FROM ontime GROUP BY Year;

schema.name: Q9
schema.sql: SELECT Year, count(*) as c1 FROM ontime GROUP BY Year;

schema.name: Q10
schema.sql: SELECT avg(cnt) FROM (SELECT Year,Month,count(*) AS cnt FROM ontime WHERE DepDel15=1 GROUP BY Year,Month) a;

schema.name: Q11
schema.sql: SELECT avg(c1) FROM (SELECT Year,Month,count(*) AS c1 FROM ontime GROUP BY Year,Month) a;

schema.name: Q12
schema.sql: SELECT OriginCityName, DestCityName, count(*) AS c FROM ontime GROUP BY OriginCityName, DestCityName ORDER BY c DESC LIMIT 10;

schema.name: Q13
schema.sql: SELECT OriginCityName, count(*) AS c FROM ontime GROUP BY OriginCityName ORDER BY c DESC LIMIT 10;
